title: Square
text:
In number theory we call an integer square-free if it is not divisible by a perfect square, except 1. You have to count them!InputFirst line contains an integerT, the number of test cases (T≤100).
The following T lines each contains one positive integer:n, where n ≤ 1014OutputTlines, on each line output the number of (positive) square-free integers not larger than n.ExampleInput:3
1
1000
100000000000000Output:1
608
60792710185947Warning: A naive algorithm will probably not be sufficient to be accepted.
